# Version Control (Conventional Commits)

## When to Use This Rule

- Apply when the user asks to:

  - Create a git commit message
  - Summarize changes for a commit
  - Prepare multiple commit messages from a diff

- Always **review the git diff** (or the user‚Äôs description of changes) before proposing a message.

## Commit Strategy

- Prefer **one logical change per commit**:

  - One bug fix
  - One feature slice
  - One focused refactor / config change

- If changes naturally split, **propose multiple commits** instead of one large commit.
- Ensure the commit message matches the **dominant intent** of the diff (feat, fix, refactor, etc.).
- Optimize messages for **changelog generation and code review** clarity.

## Commit Format

